  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: `1.5.0`\nOS & Version: Windows 10\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nCalling a constant contract method without specifying 'from' address should either return an error or use some default address, such as '0x0'\n#### Actual behaviour\n\nThe method executes with 'msg.sender' set to the first keystore's address in the node wallet, or '0x0' if no keystores are present.\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nUse 'eth_call' with no 'from' address specified, on a constant method.\ne.g.\n\n```\ncontract foo {\n    function bar () constant returns (address) {\n        return msg.sender;\n    }\n}\n```\n",
